---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Set up OCM locally in minutes — prerequisites, environment variables, and first run."
>
  <!-- ── Page hero ── -->
  <div
    class="border-b px-6 sm:px-10 lg:px-16 py-16"
    style="background-color: var(--color-porcelain); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p
        class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] mb-3"
        style="color: var(--color-gold); font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
      >
        Getting Started
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-light leading-tight mb-4"
        style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
      >
        Set up OCM locally
      </h1>
      <p
        class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
        style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
      >
        This guide walks you through cloning the repo, wiring up environment variables,
        and running both the frontend and backend on your machine.
        The full third-party provider setup and deployment are covered in the
        <a href="/tutorial" style="color: var(--color-gold); text-decoration: underline;">Tutorial</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="px-6 sm:px-10 lg:px-16 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-16">

      <!-- ── On this page ── -->
      <nav aria-label="On this page" class="border p-6 rounded-sm" style="border-color: var(--color-border); background-color: var(--color-porcelain);">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">On this page</p>
        <ol class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 list-none">
          {[
            ["Prerequisites", "#prerequisites"],
            ["Clone the Repository", "#clone"],
            ["Frontend Setup", "#frontend"],
            ["Backend Setup", "#backend"],
            ["Run Locally", "#run"],
            ["Verify It's Working", "#verify"],
          ].map(([label, href]) => (
            <li>
              <a
                href={href}
                class="toc-link text-sm transition-colors"
                style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                {label}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <!-- ── Prerequisites ── -->
      <section id="prerequisites" aria-labelledby="prereq-heading">
        <h2
          id="prereq-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Prerequisites
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <p class="text-sm mb-5" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed and accounts created.
        </p>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            {
              category: "Local tools",
              items: [
                "Node.js ≥ 22.12.0",
                "Python 3.12.x",
                "pip",
                "Git",
                "PostgreSQL (or use a free cloud instance)",
              ],
            },
            {
              category: "Third-party accounts",
              items: [
                "Firebase project (free tier is enough)",
                "Cloudinary account (free tier is enough)",
                "Paystack account (test keys work locally)",
                "YouTube Data API v3 key (for streaming page)",
              ],
            },
          ].map(({ category, items }) => (
            <div class="border p-5" style="border-color: var(--color-border); background-color: var(--color-ivory);">
              <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">{category}</p>
              <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
                {items.map((item) => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                    {item}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div
          class="mt-5 p-4 border-l-2 text-sm"
          style="border-color: var(--color-gold); background-color: var(--color-porcelain); font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
        >
          Don't have the third-party accounts set up yet? The
          <a href="/tutorial" style="color: var(--color-gold); text-decoration: underline;">Tutorial</a>
          has step-by-step instructions for each provider. You can finish the local setup
          without them, but the app won't fully authenticate until Firebase is wired up.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Clone ── -->
      <section id="clone" aria-labelledby="clone-heading">
        <h2
          id="clone-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Clone the Repository
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><code>git clone https://github.com/kibetnathan/O-Concord.git
cd O-Concord</code></pre>

        <p class="text-sm mt-4" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          The repo is a monorepo. <code>frontend/</code> is the React SPA and <code>backend/</code>
          is the Django API. They are independent apps — run them in separate terminals.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Frontend ── -->
      <section id="frontend" aria-labelledby="frontend-heading">
        <h2
          id="frontend-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Frontend Setup
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          1. Install dependencies
        </h3>
        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6"><code>cd frontend
npm install</code></pre>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          2. Create your environment file
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Create <code>frontend/.env.local</code> with the following variables. All of them come
          from the third-party accounts you'll set up in the Tutorial.
        </p>
        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"><code># Django API base URL — change to http://localhost:8000/api/ for local dev
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/

# Firebase Web SDK config (from Firebase Console > Project Settings > Your apps)
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# YouTube Data API v3 key (for the streaming/live page)
VITE_YOUTUBE_API_KEY=

# Paystack public key (use test key pk_test_... for local development)
VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=</code></pre>

        <div
          class="p-4 border-l-2 text-sm"
          style="border-color: var(--color-gold); background-color: var(--color-porcelain); font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
        >
          <strong style="color: var(--color-text-strong);">Note:</strong> The Firebase Web SDK keys
          are safe to commit — they're not secret. They identify your project but Firebase Security
          Rules control what users can actually do.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Backend ── -->
      <section id="backend" aria-labelledby="backend-heading">
        <h2
          id="backend-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Backend Setup
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          1. Install Python dependencies
        </h3>
        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6"><code>cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt</code></pre>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          2. Add your Firebase service account key
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Download your Firebase service account JSON from
          <strong>Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate new private key</strong>,
          and save it as <code>backend/firebase-key.json</code>. This file is used by Django to
          verify Firebase ID tokens on every API request.
        </p>
        <div
          class="p-4 border-l-2 text-sm mb-6"
          style="border-color: #ef4444; background-color: var(--color-porcelain); font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
        >
          <strong style="color: #ef4444;">Never commit <code>firebase-key.json</code> to git.</strong>
          It grants admin access to your Firebase project. Add it to <code>.gitignore</code> — it's already excluded in this repo.
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          3. Create your environment file
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Create <code>backend/.env</code>:
        </p>
        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6"><code># Django secret key — generate one with:
# python -c "from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())"
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

# Comma-separated — add your local dev values
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1

# PostgreSQL connection (local)
POSTGRES_DB=ocm
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=yourpassword
POSTGRES_HOST=localhost
POSTGRES_PORT=5432

# Cloudinary (from cloudinary.com > Dashboard)
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=

# Paystack (use test secret key sk_test_... for local dev)
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=

# Admin superuser created on first deploy
BACKEND_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
BACKEND_ADMIN_PASSWORD=</code></pre>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">
          4. Create the local database and run migrations
        </h3>
        <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># Create the database in psql first
psql -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE ocm;"

# Then apply Django migrations
python manage.py migrate

# Create a superuser for the Django admin panel (optional)
python manage.py createsuperuser</code></pre>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Run locally ── -->
      <section id="run" aria-labelledby="run-heading">
        <h2
          id="run-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Run Locally
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <p class="text-sm mb-5" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Open two terminals — one for each app.
        </p>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">Terminal 1 — Frontend</p>
            <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><code>cd frontend
npm run dev</code></pre>
            <p class="text-xs mt-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">Runs on http://localhost:5174</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] mb-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">Terminal 2 — Backend</p>
            <pre class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><code>cd backend
python manage.py runserver</code></pre>
            <p class="text-xs mt-2" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-khaki);">Runs on http://localhost:8000</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Verify ── -->
      <section id="verify" aria-labelledby="verify-heading">
        <h2
          id="verify-heading"
          class="text-3xl font-light mb-1"
          style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);"
        >
          Verify It's Working
        </h2>
        <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-6" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"></div>

        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          {[
            {
              check: "Frontend loads",
              how: "Open http://localhost:5174 — you should see the OCM home page.",
            },
            {
              check: "API is reachable",
              how: "Visit http://localhost:8000/api/ — Django REST Framework's browsable API should respond.",
            },
            {
              check: "Firebase is connected",
              how: "Try registering a new account. If Firebase keys are correct, the sign-up flow will complete and create a user in your database.",
            },
            {
              check: "Django admin",
              how: "Visit http://localhost:8000/admin/ and log in with the superuser you created. You should see all the OCM models.",
            },
          ].map(({ check, how }) => (
            <li class="flex gap-4 p-4 border" style="border-color: var(--color-border); background-color: var(--color-ivory);">
              <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5" style="background-color: var(--color-gold);" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 12 10" fill="none">
                  <path d="M1 5l3.5 3.5L11 1" stroke="#1a1612" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-0.5" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-strong);">{check}</p>
                <p class="text-sm" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--color-text-primary);">{how}</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Next step ── -->
      <div
        class="rounded-sm px-8 py-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-6"
        style="background-color: var(--color-gold);"
      >
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-1" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: rgba(26,22,18,0.65);">Up next</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-semibold" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; color: #1a1612;">
            Set up providers &amp; deploy
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm mt-1" style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: rgba(26,22,18,0.75);">
            Firebase, Cloudinary, Paystack, Vercel, and Render — all in one guide.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="/tutorial"
          class="shrink-0 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] px-8 py-4 transition-all"
          style="background-color: #1a1612; color: #fffef6; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
        >
          Read the Tutorial →
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .toc-link:hover { color: var(--color-gold) !important; }
    pre { tab-size: 2; }
  </style>
</DocsLayout>
